<br>
Currently, I see a lot of complaints about tanks running off and killing and not defending their casters/healers. This is a common problem, but if the tanks don't run off and kill, then the enemies come to us, surround us and kill us anyway. So, what if skalds were turned into the protect class? Basically, give us an enhanced guard/intercept that doesn't increase our own defense (block/parry) but allows us to defend another better. If our damage add range was increased to 1500 and our dd ranges increased (though not necessary for this role), we could stay back, stick/af/whatever the healer/caster, guard and intercept for them and protect them from incoming attacks. Not necessarily the most exciting role and perhaps it does lend more to the support idea, but I think it'd make us a lot more useful than the essential taxi to a fight and then either die very quickly or not do anything at all.<br>
<br>
Just a thought.. feel free to flame, support or come up with a more interesting solution.<br>
<br>
Rogenwald<br>
50 skald - Tristan <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=grigrock>GrigRock</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/27/02 12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re</span><hr size=1> I'd love to see Skalds get spec in shield. I mean why the hell can certain rogue classes spec in shield but 'light tank/support class' can't? Not that we have tons of points to spread around on it but I'd like the option personally and a medium shield would be nice too : )<br>
<br>
As for me I do my best to defend healers but without guard all we really are is an annoyance to a full tank like an armsman. Currently I ussually hunt casters and or annoy the hell out of them to buy time for the rest of the group. As a skald though I'm beginning to feel like less of a useful class and more of taxi.<br>
Roch<br>
&lt;Shield Maidens&gt;<br>
50 Skald of Palomides<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fubbor>Fubbor</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/27/02 9:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald's Role in RvR</span><hr size=1> as it is now if you try to pull that pure tank off a caster the most you do it follow him around hiting him while he owns your caster or healer then turns on you all the while your healer cant mez him cause you hiting him.  most the time I try to mez the tank on healer if that fails, like it dose 80% of the time,  then try to beat them down befor the kill you healer.  <br>
