</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=bucketoftruth>bucketoftruth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/27/02 9:17 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald's Role in RvR</span><hr size=1> I play as a tank when there are no other worthy tanks in the group.  I play mezzer and DDer when there are plenty of other tanks in the group.  When I think &quot;support class&quot; I think of going in to melee in the second wave once the real tanks have been engaged.  That way I don't draw as many enemies to me, and I can still offer a chop or two to take them down faster.  Since I started playing by these standards I've lived a lot longer in battles of all sizes. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=etzel@teamskald>Etzel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/28/02 5:53 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> sad</span><hr size=1> I think my skald's time is drawing to a close now as my SB hits high 40's. Dont get me wrong I love my kobbie but once the taxiing is done I feel like a leech in RvR. I get owned by just about everyone it seems nowadays, the final straw being a 1 on 1 vs a fire wiz. <br>
<br>
We cross paths in emain and I spot him first, I stick on him swing and dd, he faces me and starts to cast so I dd again, he tries again and I mez, it's resisted, now i'm rooted for 1min+. As he starts to make distance I snare him but he's made enough range and in comes the first bolt, I start to close and the 2nd arrives taking me to a sliver of health and crawl speed, I hit FA2 (no IP yet) and might as well not have bothered because the next nuke toasts me. <br>
<br>
I cant remember if I got 2 or 3 swings in but I was using a 99% arcanium great axe, landed both dd's and never got him past 50%. If I cant kill casters just what use do I have? <br>
<br>
As for big battles, I now normally stand at the back and pick off players with &gt; 40% damage because thats the only ones I have a chance of killing. A pretty sad state of affairs imo. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=nattfari>Nattfari</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/28/02 6:37 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Skald's role</span><hr size=1> I look at my skald as a melee class with support skills rather than a support class with melee skills.  I almost exclusively run with guild groups in RvR which means we know our jobs pretty well and usually do pretty good in RvR.  My primary job is to kill casters and bards/minstrels.<br>
<br>
I would love to see more attention paid to our melee side rather than the support one which is usually done.  A shield spec would be nice, it would make 1h/shield a viable option, and also more spec points so that our defenses could be raised somewhat.  Regarding the shield spec, scouts get it (a rogue class) but skalds don't (a viking class).  Doesnt make sense in my book really <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
We are most often compared to bards and minstrels.  Bards are naturalist class (compairable to Midgard's seer class) and minstrels are a rogue class.  Skalds are a viking class and as such should rather be compaired to paladins and wardens.  I know that wardens are a naturalist class like the bard, but they are more melee oriented and as such closer to the skald.<br>
<br>
Im not saying I want my skald to become a pure tank with support skills.  But we are of the melee class in Midgard, and I would like to have the melee skills to show for that.<br>
<br>
As to when trying to peel tanks off my casters or healers, I try to snare the tank and tell the caster or healer to run.  Usually it works so that the tank is slowed enough for his intended victim to land a stun or nuke him.  A guard/intercept option would not be viable in my opinion without a shield spec.<br>
<br>
Nattfari Eldibrandur<br>
Elding Herra of &lt;Nothing&gt;<br>
Pellinor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=tranick>Tranick</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/30/02 2:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald's role</span><hr size=1> Supposedly our equivalent in the other realms is Paladin for Alb and Warden for Hib. Supposely cause of the 'chanting' thing. What kills me is that out of all those classes only the paladin gets to spec in shield and they get 2x lvl skill points while all others in that line ie. wardens and skalds are only 1.5x lvl in skill points. Realistically I think minstrels are our equal in alb but Mythic doesn't like to compare them cause then they would have to explain stealth castable mezzes and a pet while no other class in that line gets anything like that.<br>
It's just insulting to have spent so much time lvl'ing up in the 'melee' realm only to be owned by your equilvalent class of the 'middle of the road' realm at melee.<br>
