Shield Maidens</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=kjeld>Kjeld</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 171<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/30/02 3:51 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Well ...</span><hr size=1> Role of the skald in RVR ?<br>
I don't know, I don't care anymore. I have stopped bothered, tired of beeing killed by casters in melee range (on my server, Hibernia dominates so much I think it is not even funny anymore even for them). I am not RvR ing anymore (I have won what ? maybe 2000 rps in the last month). It is that bad. The classes are poorly balanced, the realms are poorly balanced, and the promised game mechanics to help the &quot;underdog&quot; realms on server that are outrageously dominated by one realm have still not put in place. There is a limit to human beings's masochists, and when I have no fun anymore playing a flawed (in my opinion) class in an &quot;ever-losing environment&quot;, it's time to say &quot;stop&quot;. And I don't want to level to 50 with another character again, and anyway I am not a bandwagon jumper who switches to the realm/class of the month.<br>
<br>
I am having fun with my champion alt in thidranki, who *can* actually fight things, and looking forward for some nice PvE discoveries in Shrouded Isles, while waiting for AC2 (/rude MS billing system) and SWG. My RvR experience as a skald is finished. And it was not a positive one. Maybe the class was not for me, or I was not fit for the class, I don't know. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#efe0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=digitalbathe>Digital Bathe</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Participant</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/30/02 5:43 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald's Role</span><hr size=1> I've always seen a Skald as a &quot;better&quot; version of the Ministral and Bard i.e. we don't have to use instruments to make our songs better.  I also think of us as a half-tank because we can deal some decent damage (in PvE apparently) and solo yellows as far as I know so far...level 23.  Once I started RvR in BG1 I started to despise being a Skald.  You can't do crap. You can't kill casters or melees, u try running after someone when they r snared and they outrun u (please God tell me what the fuck is up with that), and never able to run away from battle since usually you never have stamina after a fight.  One way Mythic or whatever could make Skalds better is by not allowing some of their GOD DAMN songs (chants) to be interupted in combat. If i was a Skald and I was hit i wouldnt stop chanting my barbaric words, I would keep on chanting them. While a Ministral or a Bard would be screwed cuz it is...song meaning getting hit could screw their train of thought.  Anotehr thing Mythic can do is make the DD ran further out, 700 is total bullshit. Even soloing lvl 23 stuff i hate having to wait so god damn long to do DDs on them after snare pulling them.<br>
<br>
Another Question, Whatever happened to Midgard? I remember when I first got the game everyone hated Midgard because they were to strong...Now Midgard is the weakest, lease played Realm of all the servers. WTF is up with that shit is not equal at all.  On the server I play on Albions terrorize our realm along with BG1 in MASS numbers.  Hibs r not far behind with a few less in the fountier but more in bg1.  Mythic needs to rethink this entire &quot;equality&quot; in the Realms.<br>
<br>
O how I cant wait for Shadowbane to come out...full PvP with dynamic fortresses and such.<br>
<br>
Yeah overall why would anyone play as a Skald other then the speed song, damage song, and heal song. Overall I might just quit cuz now that I know what RvR has I hate it and nothing to look forward to.<br>
<br>
Thok Darksong<br>
Level 23 Troll Skald<br>
Lords of Midgard<br>
Lancelot<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://www.hamfriedchicken.com/skald">www.hamfriedchicken.com/skald</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/bteamskald.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gisborne>gisborne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Fervent</span><br>  Posts: 191<br> <font color=#ff0000>(11/30/02 2:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=413.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Skald's Role</span><hr size=1> I see a lot of complaining here, but not much to justify it. I remember the time I killed an orange con caster and an orange con ranger, solo. The time I killed a yellow wizard solo 2x in a row after I got rooted both times. I remember the time I killed a yellow con champ in 2 hits + 2DDs. I remember racking up 15k RPs in 3-4 hours, 2 days in a row thanks in part to my speed. I remember killing that 50 warden with only my DD shouts, never landing a hit once while he used FA1 and I used nothing.<br>
<br>
For everyone that kills in RvR, someone dies. You can't go running around expecting to always be on the winning end. Some days are good, some days are bad. The only reason I'm frustrated with RvR at the moment is because I can't get a hold of the jewelry I need to make my SC gear. <br>
<br>
